Description: Ostracon, fragment of the upper-body of a red-brown pottery vessel, the interior is covered with a dark-brown resinous deposit, the exterior is covered with a self-slip and very faint traces of at least four lines of black-painted demotic text.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (393767) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/393767)
